googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Stephanie K
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: I cannot say enough about Veterans plumbing. We were a victim of these crazy freezing temps and our laundry room pipe busted late Christmas afternoon. I called several plumbers and someone recommended Nick with Veterans. I called him and he answered on Christmas Day and said he could send someone out the next day. Every other plumber was Tuesday or Wednesday the earliest. They showed up early too and the value compared to what I have paid before was unbeatable. I had to ask Nick if the price was correct before I paid, as it was the best price I have seen in sometime. I am so glad I received this recommendation and they will definitely be my new plumbers of choice going forward!
googleReviewsBySlug.json.title: Veteran Plumbing LLC

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Greg King
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: We were building a garage apartment that had no plumbing or water to the structure. After several quotes, we decided to go with veteran plumbing. Nick was great to work with and very professional. The quality of work was top notch. I had concerns over locating and running water to the apartment, but Nick very professionally located the water line and was able to determine the best options to correctly run the water line to the new structire. I am very pleased with the service and finished product that Nick provided. I would highly recommend him and he will be my first call when I need future work. Great experience
googleReviewsBySlug.json.title: Veteran Plumbing LLC

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: David Barber
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: Nick is a professional in all definitions of the word professional. We have used him on multiple occasions for different plumbing needs.  A true Veteran and brother in arms who stands by his country and his work 110%.

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Alan Billingsley
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: Nick had been great working with us. Quality work, he has done work for us and our children with on time service  and competitive prices. What impresses me most is he uses top notch materials and has always let us know what he wants to do and it has always been in our best interest. We have postponed work to make sure we use him instead of others. Highly recommend, if you have an opportunity use Nick/ Veterans Plumbing LLC
googleReviewsBySlug.json.title: Veteran Plumbing LLC

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Garry Clark
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: Nick replaced a faulty hot water heater and PRV on short notice. His work ethic and expertise was impressive and commendable.  I typically value quality of work over price, but with Nick, you get both. I will call on his skills again and highly recommend his services.
googleReviewsBySlug.json.title: Veteran Plumbing LLC

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Marble House Coffee
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: Veteran Plumbing installed all the plumbing for my brand new coffee house in Acworth. It was a huge job. Nick is incredibly responsive, has extremely competitive pricing (I priced 3 different companies), and does wonderful, clean work. My job had to be inspected by the county, and they never had any issues with Nick's work. He is also enjoyable to be around, which is a bonus! Save yourself some time and call Nick for your job. You'll be glad you did!
googleReviewsBySlug.json.title: Veteran Plumbing LLC

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: hans ellison
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: Nick did a great job on our kitchen ceiling leak. There were three holes that needed to be repaired, and another pipe that was questionable. He replaced all 3 pipes, plus the 4th for no additional charge.  Very professional and uses the best equipment for the job. 4 patches done in under an hour.
googleReviewsBySlug.json.title: Veteran Plumbing LLC

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Marc Rusterucci
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: Nick and The Veteran Plumbling LLC Team are true life savers. Each time we call, there is no job too big and there is no job too small. No matter the time of day, they are there to answer the call and provide complimentary diagnostics by phone. There is no greater value than Free Advice. And, there is no greater company than Veteran Plumbing LLC.
googleReviewsBySlug.json.title: Veteran Plumbing LLC

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Nicole Hall
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text: Fabulous job Nick!  I had some serious plumbing issues in my home (prior plumbing from a different plumber that was installed incorrectly).  Nick was able to get it all fixed quickly and CORRECTLY!  Very professional and knowledgeable!  Thank you!!!
googleReviewsBySlug.json.title: Veteran Plumbing LLC

googleReviewsBySlug.json.name: Perry Kinney
googleReviewsBySlug.json.text:
You couldn't ask for a more honest and fair plummer. Nick came when he said he would and fixed my water leak. This is the second time I've used him and wouldn't think of having anyone else do any plumbing work for me. I highly recommend him as he makes sure the job is done correctly and offered no surprises when it came to his bill.
You won't be sorry. Just give him a call..
